==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tranquil
<hw>Tran"quil</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tranquillus</ets>; probably fr. <ets>trans</ets> across, over + a
word akin to <ets>quietus</ets> quiet: cf. F. <ets>tranquille</ets>. See
<er>Quiet</er>.]</ety> <def>Quiet; calm; undisturbed; peaceful; not
agitated; <as>as, the atmosphere is <ex>tranquil</ex>; the condition of
the country is <ex>tranquil</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A style clear, <qex>tranquil</qex>, easy to follow.</q>
<rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tranquillization</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Tranquilization</ent>⟦br⟧
